# packages/excalidraw conventions

This package is the published @excalidraw/excalidraw React library. Changes here ship to external consumers, so keep them conservative.

- Reuse existing React component and props patterns in this package. Match the existing stroke-style control pattern when adding new style options.
- Keep UI changes localized. Do not introduce a shared abstraction unless the plan explicitly justifies it.
- Respect package boundaries: import from @excalidraw/common, @excalidraw/element, @excalidraw/math, and @excalidraw/utils rather than reaching across with relative paths.
- Prefer behavior and accessibility assertions over snapshot-only tests.
- Follow existing test utilities and file naming in this package.
